thread.title: $A down as retail trade disappoints

title: $A down as retail trade disappoints
text:
Thu, Sep 3, 2015, 12:16 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 44 mins $A down as retail trade disappoints AAP â€“ 9 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar has lost ground after domestic retail trade figures missed expectations. 
At 1200 AEST on Thursday, the currency was trading at 70.15 US cents, down from 70.24 cents on Wednesday. 
Retail spending fell 0.1 per cent in July, worse than economists' expectations of a 0.4 per cent rise. 
It was weaker than June's 0.6 per cent rise and the first monthly fall in retail spending in more than a year. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 70.15 US cents, from 70.24 cents on Wednesday 
* 84.50 Japanese yen, from 84.29 yen 
* 62.50 euro cents, from 62.24 euro cents 
* 110.26 New Zealand cents, from 110.63 NZ cents 
* 45.83 British pence, from 45.95 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.771pct, unchanged from on Wednesday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 2.774pct, from 2.767pct 
* Sept 2015 10-year bond futures contract, at 97.270 (yield 2.730pct), down from 97.280 (2.720 pct) 
* Sept 2015 3-year bond futures contract, at 98.190 (1.810pct), down from 98.200 (1.800 pct) 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
